<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COLLEGE BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
TONIGHT'S HIGHLIGHT; 
</P>
<P>
NONCONFERENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEXAS TEACH (3-1) at SAN DIEGO STATE (2-2), 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State continues a four-game home stretch at the San Diego Sports 
Arena against a familiar team -- this is the third consecutive year the schools 
have met. Each has won at home, SDSU two years ago (72-63) and Texas Tech last 
year (58-43). The teams have a similar makeup in that the Red Raiders have nine 
new players and the Aztecs eight. Texas Tech is coming off a 78-77 loss to host 
Austin Peay in the championship of the Acme Boot tournament Saturday after 
defeating Portland in the opening round, 94-58, for its only victory over an 
NCAA Division I team. SDSU's only victories are against Division II Chaminade 
and UC Riverside. The Aztecs are shooting 45.2% from the field. 
