<P>
HELP NEEDED TO IDENTIFY VICTIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County coroner's department today asked for the public's help in 
identifying the body of a woman who was struck and killed while attempting to 
run across the Costa Mesa Freeway last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was struck by more than one vehicle when she attempted to cross the 
southbound lanes north of McFadden Avenue in Tustin about 5:15 p.m. Saturday, 
Deputy Maureen Albrecht said. 
</P>
<P>
Albrecht said the woman is between 40 and 45 years old; 5 feet, 2 inches, and 
122 pounds. She was wearing black wool slacks with gray stripes, a black cotton 
polo shirt and L.A. Gear tennis shoes. 
</P>
<P>
A check of the woman's fingerprints failed to determine her identity, Albrecht 
said. Anyone with information about a missing person fitting this description 
is asked to call the coroner's office at (714) 647-7400. 
</P>
