<P>
GERMAN CAR VENTURE PROPOSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WOLFSBURG, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
West German car maker Volkswagen said today it has proposed forming a joint 
venture with a state-owned East German vehicles producer. 
</P>
<P>
VW said its chairman, Carl Hahn, handed the proposal to the IFA industrial 
group, based in Karl-Marx-Stadt, which makes East Germany's Trabant car, among 
other vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
The venture could prepare the way for the joint development, production and 
sales of cars and vans, VW said. 
</P>
<P>
East Germany currently bans Western investment, but East Berlin officials say 
constitutional changes planned for next year will include laws allowing joint 
ventures with the West. 
