BEATRIX POTTER DRAWINGS FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three watercolor drawings by children's writer Beatrix Potter have been 
discovered in a Gloucestershire farm house and will be offered at auction Dec. 
14. The 1896 pictures of Cecily Parsley the Rabbit, a character in her Peter 
Rabbit books, have lain undiscovered in a picture album once owned by the 
writer, auctioneer Simon Bruton said. Potter died in 1943. 
