<TEXT>
<P>
The right arm of Argentine motorboat racing champion Daniel Scioli was severed 
today in an accident during the second phase of an international race along the 
Parana River, the Argentine coast guard said. 
</P>
<P>
Scioli, 34, a two-time European champion, won the first phase of the Argentine 
Delta 1,000-kilometer race Sunday, with Argentine President Carlos Saul Menem 
as his co-pilot. 
